description:
ABSTRACT  

 &nbsp; 

 The present study was conducted to know the protein, DNA. RNA and amino acids level in the stomach of male swiss albino mice infected orally each with 500 (group A), 1000 (group B) and 2000 (group C) larvae of  Ancylostoma caninum . All the mice of infected groups showed increased level of protein, RNA and amino acids and decreased level of DNA from day 1 to 30 of infection period compared to uninfected controls. It was understood that the infection induced significant alteration in the synthesis and/or release of those biochemical constituents.

